            <h1>What is accessibility?</h1>
             <section class=3D"content-section">
   =20
    <ul class=3D"prev-next"><li class=3D"menu"><a class=3D"button secondary=
" href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Co=
re/Accessibility"><span class=3D"button-wrap"> Overview: Accessibility on t=
he web</span></a></li><li class=3D"next"><a class=3D"button secondary" href=
=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Core/Acc=
essibility/Tooling"><span class=3D"button-wrap"> Next  </span></a></li></ul=
>
<p>This article starts the module off with a good look at what accessibilit=
y is =E2=80=94 this overview includes what groups of people we need to cons=
ider and why, what tools different people use to interact with the web, and=
 how we can make accessibility part of our web development workflow.</p>
<figure class=3D"table-container"><table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th scope=3D"row">Prerequisites:</th>
      <td>Familiarity with <a href=3D"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/d=
ocs/Learn_web_development/Core/Structuring_content">HTML</a>, <a href=3D"ht=
tps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Core/Styling_b=
asics">CSS</a>.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th scope=3D"row">Learning outcomes:</th>
      <td>
        <ul>
          <li>The point of accessibility =E2=80=94 increased access to digi=
tal services for those with additional needs, improved usability for everyo=
ne, better SEO, and a wider target audience.</li>
          <li>Awareness of the legal requirements of accessibility.</li>
          <li>That accessibility should be considered from the start of a p=
roject, and not bolted on at the end.</li>
          <li>Familiarity with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WC=
AG) conformance criteria.</li>
          <li>Awareness of accessibility APIs and their purpose.</li>
        </ul>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></figure>
  </section>
